      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Ansys Mechanical verification against NAFEMS benchmarks LE1, LE3, and LE10 with errors <1%.",
      "rationale": "Ansys Mechanical verified against NAFEMS linear elastic benchmarks LE1 (plane stress), LE3 (plate bending), and LE10 (3-D solid). Maximum observed deviation 0.4%. Nonlinear material subroutine verified against closed-form Ramberg-Osgood solution for Ti-6Al-4V; error <0.8% at 1.5× yield strain."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Richardson extrapolation GCI <5% for all three QoIs on production mesh.",
      "rationale": "Three-level mesh refinement study performed (coarse: 42 k elements, medium: 168 k elements, fine: 672 k elements). Richardson extrapolation applied; Grid Convergence Index for stiffness 1.8%, yield force 2.3%, force at 40 mm 2.9%. All below 5% threshold. Production mesh corresponds to medium refinement level; fine mesh results confirm asymptotic convergence (apparent order p=1.97)."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Newton-Raphson residual norm <1×10⁻⁶ at each load step; energy balance error <0.1%.",
      "rationale": "Implicit Newton-Raphson solver with line-search damping employed. Force residual norm converged to <1×10⁻⁷ at each of 200 equal load increments. Energy balance error monitored throughout simulation; maximum 0.04%. No non-convergence events recorded across all 11 simulation runs."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Independent peer review of boundary condition setup and material assignment by second analyst; documented sign-off.",
      "rationale": "Boundary conditions (fixed inferior vertebral body, displacement-controlled superior loading block) independently reviewed by a second FEA analyst not involved in model construction. Material assignments cross-checked against material certificates for each lot. Peer review checklist completed and signed; no discrepancies identified. Loading fixture geometry confirmed against ASTM F1717 Figure 1 tolerances."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Continuum mechanics representation of screw-rod construct with nonlinear material and frictional contact validated against literature and internal coupon tests.",
      "rationale": "Continuum solid mechanics formulation with nonlinear isotropic hardening (Ramberg-Osgood, Ti-6Al-4V) and augmented Lagrangian frictional contact (μ=0.25, titanium-on-titanium) adopted. Model form justified by: (1) dominant deformation mode is bending of metallic components well within continuum regime; (2) coupon-level tensile specimens validated elastic modulus and yield stress to within 3%; (3) contact formulation validated against analytical Hertz solution for cylindrical contact. Bone substitute (UHMWPE blocks) modeled as linear elastic; material constants from supplier datasheet confirmed by independent DMA testing."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "All material and geometric inputs traceable to lot-specific measurements or certified material test reports.",
      "rationale": "Screw and rod geometry digitized from CMM measurements of production lot (N=5 screws, N=3 rods); dimensional deviations from nominal <0.03 mm. Ti-6Al-4V elastic modulus (E=114 GPa) and yield stress (σ_y=880 MPa) taken from lot-specific material test reports. UHMWPE elastic modulus (E=0.8 GPa) confirmed by DMA. Friction coefficient μ=0.25 from published Ti-Ti fretting literature (Galling et al., 2019). All inputs documented in model input specification sheet, revision-controlled."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "N≥10 constructs from production lots; dimensional inspection confirming conformance to drawing tolerances.",
      "rationale": "Eleven constructs assembled from production-representative components (screws lot A23-07, rods lot R23-12, UHMWPE blocks lot P23-04). All components inspected by CMM prior to assembly; 100% within drawing tolerances. Constructs assembled by trained technician following IFU torque specifications (8 N·m set screw). Two independent laboratories (FDA CDRH OSEL and DePuy Synthes R&D) each contributed specimens, providing inter-laboratory variability data."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test conditions span clinically relevant range of loading rates and environments.",
      "rationale": "Testing performed at single loading rate (5 mm/min per ASTM F1717) in ambient laboratory conditions (22°C, dry). Physiological saline environment and elevated temperature (37°C) not evaluated. This represents a known gap relative to the required level; single test condition is the primary limitation acknowledged in the COU description. Risk accepted given that Ti-6Al-4V mechanical properties are rate-insensitive in this regime and the dominant failure mode (plastic hinge) is temperature-insensitive within the physiological range."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "FEA model inputs match experimental specimen geometry and material properties to within measurement uncertainty.",
      "rationale": "FEA model geometry updated per CMM measurements of each individual specimen (screw OD, rod diameter, inter-screw distance). Material properties assigned from lot-specific MTRs applicable to tested components. Equivalency confirmed by overlay of FEA mesh cross-sections against CMM point clouds; maximum geometric deviation 0.04 mm. Input parameter equivalency table documented in validation report Appendix B."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison using E/uval metric; threshold E/uval < 1.96 for all three QoIs.",
      "rationale": "Three QoIs compared: construct stiffness (E/uval=1.41), yield force (E/uval=1.18), force at 40 mm (E/uval=1.62). All below 1.96 threshold. Mean absolute percentage error across QoIs: 5.1%, 4.7%, 6.3%. Bland-Altman analysis confirms no systematic bias (limits of agreement symmetric about zero). Output comparison methodology follows FDA guidance on computational modeling (2021)."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs directly linked to clinical failure modes and regulatory submission requirements.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness governs load sharing with the fusion segment; yield force is the primary fatigue-relevant metric for cyclic loading predictions; force at 40 mm displacement corresponds to post-yield deformation capacity. All three are required outputs in FDA guidance for spinal implant 510(k) submissions. Clinical relevance confirmed by literature review (Rohlmann et al., 2001; Goel et al., 2006)."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation test configuration matches COU geometry, loading mode, and boundary conditions.",
      "rationale": "Validation activities directly replicate the COU: same non-cannulated 7.5 mm screw design, same ASTM F1717 compression-bending configuration, same UHMWPE bone surrogate, same inter-screw distance (44 mm). Loading mode (compression-bending) is the primary in vivo loading mode for lumbar pedicle screws. Validation samples drawn from production-representative lots. The only deviation from COU is the single test condition limitation documented under Test conditions factor."
    }
